Testing:
--------
    - Karma is the test runner internally uses "jasmine"
      framework to write the unit test cases.

    - we have two types of testings

        1. Manual Testing

        2. Automation Testing

            Unit Test Cases

            Integrated Test Cases

            End to End Test Cases

Unit Test Cases:
----------------
    - Testing the perticular functionality with dummy
      scenarioes like dummy services, dummy api,...
      called as Unit Testing.


Integrated Test Cases:
----------------------
    - Testing the Perticular Functionality with Actual
      Scenarioes called as Integrated Test Cases.


end to end test cases:
----------------------
    - Testing the Perticular Application with Different
      End Points with Actual Scenarioes called as
      e2e testing.


Installation Of Karma:
----------------------
>npm install -g karma

var app = angular.module("app",[]);
app.controller("ctrl",ctrl);
function ctrl($scope){
    $scope.var_one="Welcome";
}

karma.conf.js
-------------
describe("first test case",function(){
    var $controller;
    module("app");
    inject("getting controller",function(_$controller_){
        $controller=_$controller_;
    });
});


test.ts
-------
it("testing the controller",function(){
    var result = $controller.get("ctrl",{$scope:$scope});
    expect(result.var_one).equals("Welcome")
        console.log("Test Case Success !");
});




